defaultQ25 default&#xa0; 
defaultMr Binley:default They are, in our river valley.  We all have our own little part of the world.  
defaultDavid Hargreavesdefault: Of course, right.  They may have to move on.  
defaultMr Binley: default 
defaultAnd mess somebody else’s river valley up.
defaultDavid Hargreavesdefault: Yes.  With aggregate, though, you create a huge hole in the ground.  We are, in certain parts of the country, short of landfill.  You have to be careful with landfill—what you put in and how you put it in—but it can be restored.  Unlike something like a coal mine, where half of it goes back on
default 
defaultto waste tips, all aggregate is effectively mined and taken away.  It is a moving feast.  
